g strings!"],[221,"Providing a few colors in the `gradientColors` array will result in each bar getting a linear gradient with evenly spaced stops based on the number of colors given."],[69,"Quick Start"],[72,"Quick Start"],[275,"Quick Start"],[380,"Quick Start"],[165,"Radar charts"],[239,"Regardless, here's a table & visual guide for all placement options!"],[28,"Removed `classes` option from all charts"],[26,"removed `linkedom` dependency, now just using strings for charts"],[56,"Removed some console logs from `linechart`"],[29,"replacing with sensible default classes applied to chart elements"],[229,"Results in:"],[374,"Results in:"],[41,"Revamped labeling system:"],[89,"Roadmap"],[116,"Rough list of features I'd like to add:"],[164,"Scatter plots"],[30,"See Charts Classes for more info"],[114,"Simple to use"],[263,"Simple usage for simple results"],[361,"Simple usage for some simple line charts."],[280,"Size & Spacing"],[385,"Size & Spacing"],[354,"Smooth Line"],[105,"So just as disclaimer, this is not set in stone! And there's no definitive dates for when or if pieces of what's here will arrive. As of now this whole thing is just, and while I'd like to make time for it - things don't always go the way you want day to day. Instead of a concrete roadmap, this is more of a ideas page, with a few categories - &#x2A;*definite,** &#x2A;*maybe,** and **no**."],[190,"So that line graph though is within it's own cell, not floating on the sheet. And how does `SPARKLINE` come into play? Well, that's all it takes!"],[193,"So why toomanycharts? Time! I hope to create something that saves developers time,I want a library that can make meaningful simple charts, with trivial effort required. I hope this library is something more of a useful tool for quick & simple chart creation, whether it be a small panel in an admin dashboard, a placeholder until there's time to create a better chart, or even a debugging tool."],[176,"Some of my favorites:"],[154,"Some sort of hover-tooltip